24 Jul 2017 06:21






I don't really know how to feel about this. For one, it doesn't strike me as a -J - it seems like the doctor or someone could easily have just needed something to write instructions on so it grabbed this off the top of some forms. The idea is nice, and I like the way it's written, particularly how it's not so serious as to lose the attractive lighthearted tone, nor so whacky as to lose any sense of setting or tone. I feel compelled to upvote mostly because I just haven't read anything like this on the wiki before; it's refreshingly unique and for that reason alone I approve of it very heartily. Should you decide to remove and/or rework this I would, tenatively, recommend getting rid of that ambiguity and work on making this a strictly formal work set in a period where anomalous pets are taboo and regulated heavily but not necessarily illegal, or on the flipside just get rid of the pretenses and focus on the laughs, which I found to be distinctly lacking as a rule of thumb.





