This is a sort of neat idea - an SCP being treated like a pet/child - but I never actually laughed at anything. Like, it's sort of cute in places, but the execution just falls flat.

The framing is weird too. Is the person who wrote this connected to the Foundation or what?

As Roget commented, I think this idea would work better outside the SCP format, just have it be a note left for a petsitter or something.







